editorialSummary.text: Drugstore & pharmacy chain selling products including cosmetics, vitamins & mini-mart basics.

originalText.text:
There are very rude and unprofessional staff at this pharmacy. Every time I went to pick up my prescription, they talked to me like I was a drug dealer or something. They told me that I had to come to pick up my medication on a specific day, and when I went to get my prescribed medications, they told me they did not have it. They could have said to me that they could not do my prescribed medication when I went there days before, so I had my doctor send it to a different pharmacy. Still, they choose not to provide information to their clients, and the way the pharmacists respond to their questions is unprofessional and with attitude.
Moreover, when you call the pharmacy to have a prescription ready, they keep you on hold for at least one hour

originalText.text: Only come here to pick up medicine at the pharmacy. The young lady at the counter gave slightly annoyed vibes when I tried to sign for my prescription. Not used to having to go through so many steps just to get my medicine. Extremely high prices and long lines after 5PM. I also had to SHOW ID just to purchase a bottle of Tylenol liquid cough medicine.

originalText.text: Came for a vaccine appointment 15 minutes early per their website, checked in, and was told to take a seat and wait to be called. I waited for over an hour (including asking someone at the 30 minute mark and being told I would be called soon), when another staff member asked me why I was waiting. Why did you sign me in if you weren’t going to put me in the queue?? When I was finally added to the list, they put me at the end of the queue. About half a dozen people who arrived after me, including someone who was an hour early for their appointment, all got their vaccines while I waited. Another person who arrived after me was being called when I straight up begged for my vaccine as I had been waiting for nearly an hour and a half and needed to go home. The vaccine took 15 seconds. I waited an hour and 20 minutes for a shot that took less than one minute. I feel like there is no good excuse for this.

originalText.text:
This pharmacy accidentally deleted one of my prescriptions and being that I have experience as a pharmacist and pharmacy assistant and MD, I tried to patiently walk them through where they could check for it knowing for a fact that it had at some point been processed and dispensed (because I had come to the pharmacy to pick it up and had the actual pill bottle in my hands).

The pharmacy assistant was flippant and snide, and said do you want to speak to the pharmacist like that was a threat. It took a little navigating but we found that my prescription did in fact exist and that it was cancelled into non-existence instead of being cancelled and placed back on file to be filled another day. Getting that explanation was like pulling teeth, which has me questioning their transparency, but I had to be clear about who was at fault and frankly the amount of time and effort it took to get that answer was disappointing.

Not a life or death situation, but poor customer service and unprofessional conduct.
